<section class="about-prose" aria-labelledby="about-title">
    <div class="admin-header">
        <div>
            <div class="wf-eyebrow">OPEN SOURCE / EXPERIMENTAL / HUMAN</div>
            <h1 class="admin-title" id="about-title">A small internet to build and learn in.</h1>
            <p class="admin-sub">Tommy’s Club is a passion project for trying thoughtful social features in public.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p class="lead">Tommy’s Club is a place for writing, conversation, and the occasional idea that does not fit neatly into a feed.</p>

    <p>This website is open source because the process is part of the project. It is being used to test ideas around identity, privacy, realtime chat, media, and community without pretending that every idea is finished.</p>

    <p>It is not built for maximum reach or endless scrolling. The hope is simpler: make a small space that feels considered, learn from the rough edges, and leave useful pieces behind for anyone curious enough to look around.</p>

    <p>You can use an alias, choose how much of yourself to share, write something long, reply to someone, or send a thought to The Room. What matters here is the quality of the exchange, not the size of the audience.</p>

    <h2 id="about-features">What you can try</h2>
</section>

<ul class="feature-grid" aria-labelledby="about-features">
    <li class="feature-item"><i class="bi bi-pencil-square" aria-hidden="true"></i>&nbsp; Write posts and keep drafts private</li>
    <li class="feature-item"><i class="bi bi-chat-square-text" aria-hidden="true"></i>&nbsp; Talk in The Room in realtime</li>
    <li class="feature-item"><i class="bi bi-person-badge" aria-hidden="true"></i>&nbsp; Use a pseudonymous profile</li>
    <li class="feature-item"><i class="bi bi-lock" aria-hidden="true"></i>&nbsp; Keep personal details private</li>
    <li class="feature-item"><i class="bi bi-image" aria-hidden="true"></i>&nbsp; Share responsive, optimized media</li>
    <li class="feature-item"><i class="bi bi-bezier2" aria-hidden="true"></i>&nbsp; Notice the small interaction experiments</li>
</ul>

<section class="about-prose about-details" aria-labelledby="about-references">
    <h2 id="about-references">Made to learn in public</h2>
    <p>The visual language mixes CRT nostalgia with 1990s editorial design: newsprint tones, pixel labels, hard shadows, bright registration marks, and typography that makes room for longer reading. The application UI stays modern and restrained so the personality does not get in the way of the words.</p>

    <h2>References and influences</h2>
    <p>Some interaction ideas were informed by <a href="https://kokonutui.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Kokonut UI<span class="visually-hidden"> (opens in a new tab)</span></a>, especially its avatar, dropdown, and loader patterns. The navigation takes a cue from X/Twitter, while post media behavior is informed by social reading experiences such as Reddit and X/Twitter. UI/UX Pro Max, Site Architecture, and HyperFrames guidance also helped shape the design and motion decisions.</p>
    <p>These are references for learning and discussion. Tommy’s Club does not claim to reproduce their branding or source code.</p>
</section>

